{
  "texts": [
    "To combat the frequency selectivity, Ozkaptan et al. [166] proposed an adaptive waveform design scheme for the OFDM-based ISAC, where the complex weights of sub-carriers were optimized according to the communication and sensing channels.",
    "However, the OFDM waveform suffers from the challenges of high PAPR and sidelobes.",
    "To address this issue, Huang et al. [167] proposed a novel low-PAPR OFDM waveform for ISAC by sub-carrier optimization.• OTFS-based waveform design.",
    "Compared to OFDM, OTFS, another promising communication waveform, is more suitable for the high mobility environment due to its high Doppler tolerance [105].",
    "Specifically, OTFS modulates data in the Doppler-delay domain rather than the time-frequency domain, enabling it to accommodate the time-varying channels in high-mobility scenarios [33]."
  ]
}